args: (The Qilin I know are all fine,\nnoble people.)

(But...the way they follow their own path,
not caring what others think...is kind of
the same? Could it be they're really all
like him?)
Don't just stand there!\nThe match is startin'!
Phew! I was worried there for a sec.
I think she's thinking about Wu Wei\nand having a hard time concentrating.
Guess so—although looks like you and\nher both advance to the semifinals.
I figured he'd win, but boy, did he EVER!
Which means he'll be fighting\n{player_name} in the semifinals.
I know how remarkable your skills are.
But now that I've come this far,\nI don't intend to lose!
Oh, I would expect nothing less.\nI have high hopes for you.
Tomorrow is the day I take on Wu Wei.
If you keep stressing about the upcoming\nbattle, you shall wear yourself out before\nit can even commence.
She's right. Leave things here in the castle\nto us—you turn in early and get some rest.
I guess that makes sense. Tha—
Bad news, everyone! Elma Village is\nbein' attacked by fiends!
We need to head there right away!
Wait a second. Is that really a good idea?!
Good or not, the village is being attacked,\nwhich means we have to help.
But Elma Village is an age from here!\nIf you go, you'll never make it back\nin time for your tournament match.
And even if you WERE on time, you'll be\nin no condition to fight Wu Wei.
Lin You, listen to me. I know we both\nseek the same thing: to become strong.
But I want to be strong so I can protect\neveryone who lives in the kingdom.
So right now, all that matters is the\nsafety of that village and its people.
Come on, everyone. Let's move out.
With his opponent absent, competitor\nWu Wei is the victor by default!
The boy ran away, did he? Pathetic.
...So it's all well and good we pushed\nthrough our fatigue and got here,\nbut there ain't nobody around.
I suppose that's to be expected.\nIt's long past dark, after all.
If you knew that, why did we haul tail\nall the way here? I'm freakin' EXHAUSTED!
But if someone really had been\nwaiting for us, it would've been\nrude not to show up.
Why are you showing your face here now?
I expected the rest of those cowards to\nflee from a fight, but not you.
Then why did he miss our bout?
How 'bout you shut yer pie hole for once\nand have yer little match right now?
If all ya want is a fight, it don't have to\nbe part of some organized tournament.
I will not deign to field a challenge from\na weakling. There is no value in it.
Nor will I sully my hands tangling with a\ncoward. There is even less value in that\nthan fighting a weakling.
How can you stand there while he says\nthose things, {player_name}?!
He's right. Well, maybe not RIGHT,\nbut it's true that I missed the match.
But the way he talked about you!
Words are trivial compared to how we\nprotected the people of Elma Village.
Even if I didn't beat Wu Wei,\nmy strength still had meaning.
Then what is the meaning\nof MY strength...?
